Eva - Love your video's, But I would like to offer a Canadian perspective to your camping recommendations. Never leave your food (or toothpaste for that matter) inside your tent or near your tent unless you want an unpleasant visitor during the night. Just a suggestion from an experienced Canadian camper.
Keep up the great video's, your a natural.
Cheers

Canadian here too and I thought the EXACT same thing about the food!! lol You never keep your food in your tent unless it's absolutely necessary and the food is being stored in air locked, extremely tight containers. Even better when said food containers have been certified animal proof. That's one of the first and most basic rules of camping you learn as a child and I was really surprised that Eva didn't know that.
